🗄️ SQL Basics (Database Queries)

SQL is used to interact with databases.

📊 Basic SELECT Queries
Select all data:
SELECT * FROM Orders;
* means all columns
🍽️ Select Specific Columns
SELECT drink, price FROM Orders;
Returns only selected columns
🔍 Filtering Data (WHERE)
SELECT * FROM Orders
WHERE drink = 'Coffee';
Filters results based on condition
📉 Sorting Data (ORDER BY)
SELECT * FROM Orders
ORDER BY price;
Sorts from lowest to highest
📊 Descending Order
SELECT * FROM Orders
ORDER BY price DESC;
Sorts from highest to lowest
💰 Filtering by Price
SELECT * FROM Orders
WHERE price <= 200;
Shows only cheap items

🧠 Key Takeaways:
Linux and Windows command lines are essential for system control
File navigation and searching are critical in cybersecurity
SSH allows remote system access (often targeted by attackers)
Weak passwords and misconfigurations lead to privilege escalation
SQL is used to interact with databases and extract information
Understanding queries helps in detecting database vulnerabilities
